The question to me is if using the blocking executor is so tempting for us developers that it's worth adding this check. (I haven't tested if it has any effect on the build time, but I always felt like CheckStyle is taking too long :)) It's not like CompletableFuture.*Async(), where it's very easy to slip and use the wrong overload, here it's obvious both for the author and for the reviewer when a reference to the blocking executor is added.
For existing references, I don't think this
   // To be removed with https://issues.redhat.com/browse/ISPN-11483
   @SuppressWarnings("checkstyle:RegexpSinglelineJava")

is any more clear than
   // TODO To be removed with https://issues.redhat.com/browse/ISPN-11483

